title: CLIMBING the HIGHEST Mountain in NORTH AFRICA // MT. TOUBKAL, Morocco 4167m ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ∫ÿ±ÿ®
description:
Mt. Toubkal is one of the most insane adventures that I have ever embarked on. When your friend's crampon snaps in half and his head torched blows off at 5am in the pitch dark when you're standing on ice on the side of a the tallest mountain in North Africa, let me just say that it's not the most pleasant experience. But it when all was said done, it transformed into one of the most pleasant. Thank you for watching vlog #73 - The 24 Minute MT. Toubkal Special Feature.

title: KILLING FIELDS, PHNOM PENH, CAMBODIA
description: Vlog #25. I visit The Killing Fields of Choeung Ek in Phnom Penh, Cambodia. The Killing Fields are a number of sites in Cambodia where collectively more than a million people were killed and buried by the Khmer Rouge regime, during its rule of the country from 1975 to 1979, immediately after the end of the Cambodian Civil War (1970‚Äì1975). The mass killings are widely regarded as part of a broad state-sponsored genocide (the Cambodian genocide).

title: A three month Journey through India & Nepal, featuring an Earthquake
description:
This is my first hand experience of travelling around Northern India, over to Nepal and trekking to Mt Everest Base Camp. After this spectacular experience, I head to Tripureshwor-6 (a remote village in Nepal) to teach english at a small school. I am spending time with the beautiful native people when the devastating 7.8 magnitude earthquake of April 25 2015 strikes. From here I try to help in a small way by travelling to Pokhara (Nepal's second largest city) to gather supplies and return to the village. After doing what I can, I head back to the capital city of Katmandu where yet another huge earthquake hits. Please excuse some of the shaky footage. Watch in HD.

Donations to UNICEF to assist with prevention of child trafficking in Nepal which has increased dramatically since the earthquakes of 2015: 
https://www.unicef.org.nz/nepal?gclid=CNDJ9czBlcwCFYeYvAod5kcAGA

Thanks for watching, Nick.
